<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Tonle Sap River and Lake, and most tributaries (locality no. 3, 6, 7, 8, 11, 12, 16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23, 24, 27, 32, 38, 39 and 40). Buried just below surface of soft, muddy substrate of the water bodies.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Approximately 17 different species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ng &amp; Jeratthitikul &amp; Sutcharit &amp; Chhuoy &amp; Pin &amp; Pholyotha &amp; Siriwut &amp; Srisonchai &amp; Hogan &amp; Ngor" authorityYear="2020" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyrenidae" genus="Corbicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Corbicula" order="Venerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Corbicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have previously been recorded from Cambodia (Suppl. material 1: Table S1), but there has been no known attempt to verify if all are valid records. In neighbouring Thailand, 21 nominal 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ng &amp; Jeratthitikul &amp; Sutcharit &amp; Chhuoy &amp; Pin &amp; Pholyotha &amp; Siriwut &amp; Srisonchai &amp; Hogan &amp; Ngor" authorityYear="2020" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyrenidae" genus="Corbicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Corbicula" order="Venerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Corbicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species were all found to belong to only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="O. F. Müller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyrenidae" genus="Corbicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Corbicula fluminea" order="Venerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fluminea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Corbicula fluminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(OF 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
, 1774), a single species (
<bibRefCitation author="Kijviriya, V" journalOrPublisher="American Malacological Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="97 - 106" refId="B37" refString="Kijviriya, V, Upatham, ES, Viyanant, V, Woodruff, DS, 1991. Genetic studies of Asian clams, Corbicula, in Thailand: allozymes of 21 nominal species are identical. American Malacological Bulletin 8 (2): 97 - 106" title="Genetic studies of Asian clams, Corbicula, in Thailand: allozymes of 21 nominal species are identical." volume="8" year="1991">Kijviriya et al. 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Based on morphological examination of the fresh material from the Tonle Sap basin, it is possible that there may be more than one 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ng &amp; Jeratthitikul &amp; Sutcharit &amp; Chhuoy &amp; Pin &amp; Pholyotha &amp; Siriwut &amp; Srisonchai &amp; Hogan &amp; Ngor" authorityYear="2020" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyrenidae" genus="Corbicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Corbicula" order="Venerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Corbicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species present. However, further investigation including molecular analysis will be required to confirm the species identities (
<bibRefCitation author="Bieler, R" editor="Lydeard, C" journalOrPublisher="Johns Hopkins Press, Maryland" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="187 - 192" refId="B4" refString="Bieler, R, Mikkelsen, PM, 2019. Cyrenidae Gray, 1840. In: Lydeard, C, Cummings, KS, Eds., Freshwater Mollusks of the World: A Distribution Atlas. Johns Hopkins Press, Maryland: 187 - 192" title="Cyrenidae Gray, 1840." volumeTitle="Freshwater Mollusks of the World: A Distribution Atlas." year="2019">Bieler and Mikkelsen 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ng &amp; Jeratthitikul &amp; Sutcharit &amp; Chhuoy &amp; Pin &amp; Pholyotha &amp; Siriwut &amp; Srisonchai &amp; Hogan &amp; Ngor" authorityYear="2020" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyrenidae" genus="Corbicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Corbicula" order="Venerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Corbicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are the only bivalves that are commercially harvested from the Lake to be sold locally and exported abroad for human consumption and as animal feed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Freshwater mollusc fisheries at the Tonle Sap Lake, Cambodia. Small-scale harvesting of freshwater molluscs A Corbicula spp. and B Mekongia rattei, at open areas of the Lake. Freshwater molluscs C Corbicula spp. and D Pila spp., being sorted and packed at main landing sites around the Lake. Photographs by A Pholyotha (A, B), TH Ng (C), PB Ngor (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.958.53865.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441307" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">4A, C</figureCitation>
). More than 6000 tonnes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ng &amp; Jeratthitikul &amp; Sutcharit &amp; Chhuoy &amp; Pin &amp; Pholyotha &amp; Siriwut &amp; Srisonchai &amp; Hogan &amp; Ngor" authorityYear="2020" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyrenidae" genus="Corbicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Corbicula" order="Venerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Corbicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clams were recorded from five commercial landing sites in Kampong Chhnang Province, within the Tonle Sap basin, over the period of one year (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1051/limn/2018026" author="Ngor, PB" journalOrPublisher="Annales de Limnologie-International Journal of Limnology" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="34 - 10" refId="B72" refString="Ngor, PB, Sor, R, Prak, LH, So, N, Hogan, ZS, Lek, S, 2018d. Mollusc fisheries and length-weight relationship in Tonle Sap flood pulse system, Cambodia. Annales de Limnologie-International Journal of Limnology 54: 34 - 10, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1051/limn/2018026" title="Mollusc fisheries and length-weight relationship in Tonle Sap flood pulse system, Cambodia." url="https://doi.org/10.1051/limn/2018026" volume="54" year="2018 d">Ngor et al. 2018d</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
